Posts.Content: pamj13 wrote: 40 yrs old and went for my baseline study. Findings: symmetric parenchymal pattern and mixture of fatty and fibroglandular tissue is seen. Implants are intact. Nodular density is seen in the right breast deep to the nipple, inner portion of the breast on the right CC view and measures up to 1.4cm. The borders are slightly lobulated. Would recommend spot compression and ultrasound for further evaluation. No suspicious microcalcification is seen. Left axillary lymph node is seen. Impression : 1. Right breast nodule. Recommend spot compression and ultrasound for further evaluation. 2. Implants Result: BI-RAD 0 incomplete Any and all insight in this would be Greatly appreciated. Thanks so much.
